<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      a:active, button:active {
         color: red;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p>The <b>:active</b> CSS pseudo-class represents an element that is being activated by the user. It is commonly used in links and buttons. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   <div> <button> Button </button> Go to <a href="#">nowhere</a> </div>
   <p> Try clicking them to see the effect! </p>
</body>
